00:28:45.090 --> 00:28:50.450
Glass ceiling is anything
that may not be-- well,

00:28:50.450 --> 00:28:52.210
that's exact why it's glass.

00:28:52.210 --> 00:28:55.000
Because sometimes you're
not supposed to see it.

00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:57.750
But it's somewhat
there, standing

00:28:57.750 --> 00:29:03.110
as an obstacle, as a
constraint to the progression

00:29:03.110 --> 00:29:07.400
of a woman in the
place of career,

00:29:07.400 --> 00:29:09.660
occupation, and profession.

00:29:09.660 --> 00:29:14.190
And so with glass
ceiling, there was a time

00:29:14.190 --> 00:29:18.150
in the history of the
world when it was perfectly

00:29:18.150 --> 00:29:21.550
normal for women to
have no aspiration

00:29:21.550 --> 00:29:25.580
toward any occupation,
career, or profession.

00:29:25.580 --> 00:29:32.320
And so at that time,
when the awakening begun

00:29:32.320 --> 00:29:41.700
to permeate through some set of
women, who dared to challenge

00:29:41.700 --> 00:29:44.810
that idea, that all
the woman needed to do

00:29:44.810 --> 00:29:48.320
was be a lovely
consort of a man,

00:29:48.320 --> 00:29:53.270
and sit around with other
women, just fan themselves,

00:29:53.270 --> 00:29:55.080
and have an afternoon tea.

00:29:55.080 --> 00:29:56.066
You know?

00:29:56.066 --> 00:29:59.640
When some women began
to challenge that,

00:29:59.640 --> 00:30:03.450
they needed to be able to
carry many more voices along

00:30:03.450 --> 00:30:04.690
with them.

00:30:04.690 --> 00:30:07.170
And over time, that
conversation began

00:30:07.170 --> 00:30:12.820
to happen, that what are
the barriers to this,

00:30:12.820 --> 00:30:16.430
to women being able to
fulfill their talent?

00:30:16.430 --> 00:30:20.570
And it went from just
that socialization,

00:30:20.570 --> 00:30:22.820
you know, that
solution expectation,

00:30:22.820 --> 00:30:25.630
that it was not necessary.

00:30:25.630 --> 00:30:28.980
A man could do the work,
take care of everyone.

00:30:28.980 --> 00:30:31.530
And so why are you
wasting your time,

00:30:31.530 --> 00:30:35.650
trying to do what a man can do?

00:30:35.650 --> 00:30:36.890
So you have that.

00:30:36.890 --> 00:30:41.290
You also have
religious angles to it,

00:30:41.290 --> 00:30:44.420
where some of the people
who didn't completely

00:30:44.420 --> 00:30:47.030
read their Bible
well sort of thought

00:30:47.030 --> 00:30:50.750
that when God created
Adam and Eve, he did

00:30:50.750 --> 00:30:53.970
say, to Eve, take half
the brain of Adam.

00:30:53.970 --> 00:30:57.670
There's nowhere in the scripture
that that's contained at all.

00:30:57.670 --> 00:31:02.850
So clearly, God did not have
an intention for a woman to be,

00:31:02.850 --> 00:31:06.530
in any way, less
than a human being.

00:31:06.530 --> 00:31:09.560
As a matter of fact, I
normally say to people,

00:31:09.560 --> 00:31:13.050
that in Genesis
1:26, he actually

00:31:13.050 --> 00:31:15.810
expressly, in that
conversation, said,

00:31:15.810 --> 00:31:20.470
male and female created
[INAUDIBLE] death.

00:31:20.470 --> 00:31:25.380
And then it was after that,
in 28 of that same Genesis 1,

00:31:25.380 --> 00:31:28.055
he then says, be fruitful.

00:31:28.055 --> 00:31:29.430
JULIET EHUMIAN
CHIAZOR: Multiply.

00:31:29.430 --> 00:31:30.471
OBY ESEKWESILI: Multiply.

00:31:30.471 --> 00:31:32.130
Replenish the earth.

00:31:32.130 --> 00:31:33.100
Dominate.

00:31:33.100 --> 00:31:34.500
subdue.

00:31:34.500 --> 00:31:36.120
Who was he speaking to?

00:31:36.120 --> 00:31:39.160
He was speaking to
both males and females.

00:31:39.160 --> 00:31:42.150
So if he had an intention
for any one of them

00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:46.030
to be subordinated in terms
of their intellectual capacity

00:31:46.030 --> 00:31:47.750
to be the best
that they could be,

00:31:47.750 --> 00:31:49.860
he would expressly have said it.

00:31:49.860 --> 00:31:54.760
Even though God does not speak
too often, when he speaks,

00:31:54.760 --> 00:31:58.720
he is very composed in
trying to convey his message.

00:31:58.720 --> 00:32:02.630
So religious is there,
for the human mind,

00:32:02.630 --> 00:32:04.600
where they created a barrier.

00:32:04.600 --> 00:32:09.610
And then there are certain
things that are geographical,

00:32:09.610 --> 00:32:14.100
where in certain environments,
they just need topography

00:32:14.100 --> 00:32:16.770
and the geography of
it means that there

00:32:16.770 --> 00:32:19.850
is an obstacle to women
being able to respond

00:32:19.850 --> 00:32:23.910
to some of the kind of context
within which they operate.

00:32:23.910 --> 00:32:28.070
And of course, economic,
family issues, and all of that.

00:32:28.070 --> 00:32:32.240
All these obstacles and
barriers act as glass ceiling.

00:32:32.240 --> 00:32:37.270
But when you now take
it to the micro level,

00:32:37.270 --> 00:32:41.790
a glass ceiling is whatever
exists in terms of the way

00:32:41.790 --> 00:32:46.820
that human resources
is incentivized

00:32:46.820 --> 00:32:50.331
within the workplace.

00:32:50.331 --> 00:32:54.850
And if it is incentivized
in a particular way,

00:32:54.850 --> 00:33:00.570
any part of it that hinders
the progress of women

00:33:00.570 --> 00:33:01.472
is a glass ceiling.

00:33:01.472 --> 00:33:02.680
JULIET EHUMIAN-CHIAZOR: Yeah.

00:33:02.680 --> 00:33:06.710
OBY ESEKWESILI: So if the
incentive in the workplace

00:33:06.710 --> 00:33:11.015
does not make itself amenable--

00:33:11.015 --> 00:33:12.390
JULIET EHUMIAN
CHIAZOR: Enabling.

00:33:12.390 --> 00:33:14.020
OBY ESEKWESILI: And
enabling-- that's

00:33:14.020 --> 00:33:16.900
the word-- enabling
of women, because

00:33:16.900 --> 00:33:21.790
of some of the
variations in the pattern

00:33:21.790 --> 00:33:26.660
and the lives of women that
could require the workplace

00:33:26.660 --> 00:33:28.360
to adapt.

00:33:28.360 --> 00:33:38.450
And with that adaptability, help
them to overcome those hidden

00:33:38.450 --> 00:33:39.620
barriers.

00:33:39.620 --> 00:33:42.050
Then you have a glass ceiling.

00:33:42.050 --> 00:33:45.314
So I've taken it from the global
to the macro, and then to the--

00:33:45.314 --> 00:33:46.480
JULIET EHUMIAN-CHIAZOR: Yes.

00:33:46.480 --> 00:33:48.640
OBY ESEKWESILI: To the
femme level, isn't it?

00:33:48.640 --> 00:33:50.098
JULIET EHUMIAN
CHIAZOR: Absolutely.

00:33:50.098 --> 00:33:51.280
And to the personal level.

00:33:51.280 --> 00:33:52.450
OBY ESEKWESILI: And
to the personal level.

00:33:52.450 --> 00:33:53.950
JULIET EHUMIAN-CHIAZOR: From
your own personal experience,

00:33:53.950 --> 00:33:55.690
because you're
quite accomplished.

00:33:55.690 --> 00:33:58.350
And one can say, you're a
